The mutation changes `/#.*$/` to `/#.$/` - the original removes everything from `#` to end of string, while the mutation only removes `#` followed by exactly one character. So a URL with a fragment longer than one character (like `#section`) won't be fully stripped in the mutated version.

```typescript
import { parse } from "../../../../../../../../../../../subject_repositories/crawler-url-parser/crawler-url-parser.js";

describe('parse URL with multi-character fragment', () => {
  it('should strip a fragment with multiple characters from a URL', () => {
    const result = parse("http://www.example.com/page#section");
    expect(result).not.toBeNull();
    expect(result!.url).toBe("http://www.example.com/page");
  });
});
```

The mutation changes `/#.*$/` to `/#.$/`. The original removes `#` and everything after it. The mutated version only removes `#` followed by exactly one character. So a URL with a fragment of 2+ characters like `#ab` won't be fully stripped - the mutated regex `/#.$/` won't match at all if there are more than one character after `#`, leaving the fragment in the URL.

Wait, let me reconsider. `/#.$/` matches `#` followed by exactly one character at end of string. So `#a` would be removed, but `#ab` would NOT be removed. The fragment would remain in the URL string, causing `URL.parse` to potentially include it differently.

Let me think about what happens with `http://www.example.com/page#ab` - the fragment `#ab` won't be stripped, so `URL.parse` will see it. But `delete parsedUrl.hash` is called after... so the hash is deleted from the parsed object. The result URL should still be correct.

The key is the `currentUrlStr` replacement happens BEFORE `URL.parse`. If fragment isn't stripped, `URL.parse` parses it with the fragment, but then `delete parsedUrl.hash` removes it. So the final URL should be the same...

The difference would only matter if the fragment somehow affects parsing before the hash deletion. Let me test with a URL where fragment removal matters for the path/query parsing step.

